.TH "fwserial_close_port" 9 "fwserial_close_port" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
fwserial_close_port \-  HUP the tty (if the tty exists) and unregister the tty device. Only used by the unit driver upon unit removal to disconnect and cleanup all attached ports
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" fwserial_close_port
.BI "(struct tty_driver *driver "  ","
.BI "struct fwtty_port *port "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "driver" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "port" 12
-- undescribed --
.SH "DESCRIPTION"

The port reference is put by fwtty_cleanup (if a reference was
ever taken).
